<p><a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/2015/CR-ATAG20-20150604/">Authoring Tool Accessibility Guidelines (ATAG) 2.0</a> Candidate Recommendation (CR) has been updated with simplified exit criteria to bring it more in line with common W3C practices for CR exit criteria. There are no substantive changes to ATAG 2.0 itself, only to the CR exit criteria. <a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/2015/WD-IMPLEMENTING-ATAG20-20150604/">Implementing ATAG 2.0</a> is also updated to keep cross-linking between the two documents in sync. The ATAG CR exit criteria have been simplified to demonstrate two implementations of each success criteria, which will reduce the testing burden. This update to the exit criteria will allow ATAG 2.0 to be completed more quickly. Learn more from the <a href="http://www.w3.org/WAI/intro/atag">ATAG Overview</a> and about the <a href="http://www.w3.org/WAI/">Web Accessibility Initiative (WAI)</a>.</p> <p><img src="https://www.w3.org/analytics/piwik/piwik.php?idsite=7&amp;rec=1&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2Fblog%2Fnews%2Farchives%2F4739%3Fpk_campaign%3Dfeed%26pk_kwd%3Datag-2-0-cr-updated-with-simplified-exit-criteria&amp;action_name=ATAG+2.0+CR+updated+with+simplified+exit+criteria&amp;urlref=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2Fblog%2Fnews%2Ffeed" style="border:0;width:0;height:0" width="0" height="0" alt="" /></p>
]]>
</content:encoded>
