The Tracking Preference Expression Patent Advisory Group (PAG) has published a report recommending per Option 1 of the W3C Patent Policy, that the initial concern has been resolved, enabling the Working Group to continue. W3C launches a PAG to resolve issues in the event a patent has been disclosed that may be essential, but is [&#8230;]<img src="https://www.w3.org/analytics/piwik/piwik.php?idsite=7&amp;rec=1&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2Fblog%2Fnews%2Farchives%2F4737%3Fpk_campaign%3Dfeed%26pk_kwd%3Dpatent-advisory-group-recommends-continuing-work-on-tracking-preference-expression&amp;action_name=Patent+Advisory+Group+Recommends+Continuing+Work+on+Tracking+Preference+Expression&amp;urlref=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2Fblog%2Fnews%2Ffeed" style="border:0;width:0;height:0" width="0" height="0" alt="" />
]]>
</description>
<content:encoded>
<![CDATA[
<p>The <a href="https://www.w3.org/2012/dnt-pag/">Tracking Preference Expression Patent Advisory Group (PAG)</a> has published a <a href="http://www.w3.org/2012/dnt-pag/pagreport.html">report</a> recommending per Option 1 of the <a href="http://www.w3.org/Consortium/Patent-Policy-20040205/#sec-PAG-conclude-possible">W3C Patent Policy</a>, that the initial concern has been resolved, enabling the Working Group to continue. W3C <a href="/Consortium/Patent-Policy-20040205/#sec-Exception">launches a PAG</a> to resolve issues in the event a patent has been disclosed that may be essential, but is not available under the <a href="/Consortium/Patent-Policy-20040205/#def-RF">W3C Royalty-Free licensing terms</a>. See the original <a href="http://www.w3.org/blog/news/archives/2856">announcement of the PAG</a>.</p> <p><img src="https://www.w3.org/analytics/piwik/piwik.php?idsite=7&amp;rec=1&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2Fblog%2Fnews%2Farchives%2F4737%3Fpk_campaign%3Dfeed%26pk_kwd%3Dpatent-advisory-group-recommends-continuing-work-on-tracking-preference-expression&amp;action_name=Patent+Advisory+Group+Recommends+Continuing+Work+on+Tracking+Preference+Expression&amp;urlref=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2Fblog%2Fnews%2Ffeed" style="border:0;width:0;height:0" width="0" height="0" alt="" /></p>
]]>
